  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Upper Nile and Unity, South Sudan 2013</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Primary purpose was to provide assistance to Sudanese refugees living in camps in Upper Nile and Unity States. Interventions included shelter and livelihood support, community infrastructure and conflict reduction initiatives to improve relationships between refugees and host communities. Direct beneficiaries included 3,500 refugee households who received shelter support; approximately 10,000 households who received agricultural inputs; 5,162 households engaged in tree planting; and more than 100 individuals who attended conflict management education. The provisions of community infrastructure/services such as classrooms, community centres, haffir dams and grinding mills have benefited many more.</narrative>
  </description>
